  "prompt": "If somebody is smoking weed around me, is it possible to get high off of second hand smoke?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to get \"contact high\" or secondhand high from marijuana smoke in an enclosed or poorly ventilated space. The likelihood depends on several factors:\n\n1. Concentration of smoke\n2. Duration of exposure\n3. Ventilation of the area\n4. Potency of the marijuana\n5. Amount being smoked\n\nIn well-ventilated areas, the risk is much lower. In small, enclosed spaces with heavy smoke, there is a higher chance of experiencing mild psychoactive effects or detecting THC in a drug test. However, the effects are generally much less intense compared to direct smoking.\n\nIf you're concerned about exposure, try to:\n- Increase ventilation\n- Move to a different area\n- Ask the person to smoke elsewhere\n\nIf you're in a situation where you might be subject to drug testing, prolonged exposure to secondhand marijuana smoke could potentially result in a positive test.",
